<seg id=1> South Korean Military Has Repeated Accidents. Opposition Party Calls for Defense Minister to Resign </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Reuters, Seoul, Telegram) The South Korean opposition party yesterday demanded that Defense Minister Qian Rong-zhai resign because the military sector has previously had a number of accidents, including firing an armed missile and a flare into a civilian residential area.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> According to South Korean officials, the most recent accident was an error that occurred at dawn yesterday during a military maneuver when the shell of a flare shot through two walls of the residence of an old woman. </seg>
<seg id=4> The home of the old woman is close to where missile debris fell two days ago after an explosion.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> A naval official says that the flare launched by the South Korea marine corps went farther than expected, falling into a civilian house in Kimpo. </seg>
<seg id=6> Kimpo is located west of Seoul. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The opposition Grand National Party issued a statement saying, "The defense minister must resign immediately, or (President Kim Dae-jung) must dismiss him from his post. </seg>
<seg id=8> A government not afraid of the people is not the people's government." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> The statement said: "Qian Rong-zhai is attempting to keep his post. He merely expresses regret; he holds to high an opinion of himself." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> The Ministry of Defense apologized for the missile launching accident the day before yesterday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> A naval official said that the shell of the flare passed through two walls before entering a bathroom. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> He added that the 83-year old woman is being treated for shock in a nearby hospital. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=13> Last Friday, the South Korean army accidentally launched a ground-to-air missile. The missile exploded in the air, wounding at least three civilians. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=14> According to an officer at the Ministry of Defense, a missile was launched by accident when military technicians were examining weapons systems at an air force base in Inchon, a western port city.  </seg>
<seg id=15> Inchon is 40 km away from the border between North and South Korea. </seg>
</p>
